Creating Visual Card 12

Creating visual Card for Out of State Violation and Latest Date the Data is refreshed

Steps

Out of State Violation

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select  Visual Card
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Click on % Out Of State  and place it inside the fields
  5.        General: X - Position = 0, Y - Position =506, Width = 205, Height = 97
  6.        Data Label : Color = #12239E,  Font Size = 30,  Font type = DIN
  7.        Category = OFF
  8.        Title ON ,   Text Title = "%Out of State Violation", Font Color = #FFFFFF , Background Color = #073501 , Font Size = 14 and Font Family = DIN
  9.        Border ON, Color = #E6E6E6 , Radius = 0



Steps

Last Refreshed Date

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select  Visual Card
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Click on refreshed date from Last Refreshed Date Table and place it inside the fields
  5.        General: X - Position = 0, Y - Position =617, Width = 205, Height = 97
  6.        Data Label : Color = #252423,  Font Size = 16,  Font type = DIN
  7.        Category = OFF
  8.        Title ON ,   Text Title = "Last Refreshed Date", Font Color = #FFFFFF , Background Color = #073501 , Font Size = 14 and Font Family = DIN
  9.        Border ON, Color = #E6E6E6 , Radius = 0





Check Step 9 (DAX Measure) how to create Last Refreshed Date Table or Visit the link below how we can create last refreshed date table
